/*  Two liquid phases sharing a PREDICTIVE UNIFAC activity model (no fitted
    pairs) -- the liquid-liquid flash needs >= 2 liquid phases to even attempt
    a split.  UNIFAC groups come from each component's case-local .dat
    (constant/components/water.dat, nButanol.dat -- vendored from the standard
    catalogue so this case is self-contained).

    HONEST-FAILURE NOTE (see README.md): predictive UNIFAC does NOT reproduce
    the water/1-butanol LLE gap -- it predicts one convex g_mix well and hence
    complete miscibility.  We keep the predictive model (no fabricated pair) and
    let the absence of a split be the lesson. */
components ( water nButanol );
phases
(
    { name vapor;   type vapor;  eos { model idealGas; } }
    { name liquid1; type liquid; activity { model UNIFAC; } }
    { name liquid2; type liquid; activity { model UNIFAC; } }
);
